CURSOR KEYS move the cursor around the grid
SHIFT-CURSOR will "lock" a row or column
SPACE triggers a number from active to inactive
SHIFT-SPACE (or .) locks the number
NUMBER keys highlight all digits which have that number as a factor
- e.g. "2" will highlight 2s, 4s, and 8s.
COMMAND-Z undoes the last step

CLICKING on a number toggles its activity
CLICKING on the green box locks that number
